body: This also includes some code cleanups.
I'll review this soon. I'd however like it if #11159 goes in first in order to prevent conflicts in an already very large PR.
No problem -- I'm fine waiting on the other PR.

I had actually already merged in the LB update change, but there was another one that was merged into master right before I pushed the changes to this PR.  I'll update again and see what the tests say.

Looks like there's an assertion failure triggering in the Windows Node tests.  I don't understand how it's happening, though, since I can't find a code-path that would cause that.

@murgatroid99, is there a way for me to run those tests such that the output includes the C-core logs?  If so, I can add some debug logging to try to figure out how this is happening.
